raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "code-server" %}
{% set version = "3.3.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-linux-amd64.tar.gz  # [linux]
  sha256: 57b9855b20f511e22776ee8a53d1ff30f864498814c4c0b0af3510f71d7a2969  # [linux]
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-macos-amd64.tar.gz  # [osx]
  sha256: b72b46476204b69c57df35f765c1e82d1770bc5970e2addfdbb21552e6967199  # [osx]
  folder:
    code-server

build:
  number: 1
  binary_relocation: False  # [osx]
  skip: true  # [win]

requirements:
  host:
  run:
    - nodejs >=12

test:
  commands:
    - code-server --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/cdr/code-server
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
   - code-server/LICENSE.txt
   - code-server/ThirdPartyNotices.txt
  summary: 'Run VS Code on a remote server.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xhochy
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
